##############################################

DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "MathObjects.pl",
  "PGML.pl",
  "contextPercent.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl",
);

##############################################

Context("Numeric");

$a=random(21,29,1)/100;
$b=random(61,69,1)/100;

$aP=$a*100;
$bP=$b*100;

Context("LimitedPercent-strict");
$ans1 = Compute("$aP %");
$ans2 = Compute("$bP %");


##############################################

TEXT(beginproblem());

BEGIN_PGML

Convert the following decimals into percentages:

    [`` [$a] = ``] [_____]{$ans1}

    [`` [$b] = ``] [_____]{$ans2}

END_PGML

##############################################

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION

To change a decimal to a percentage, we move the decimal point to the right twice.

    [` [$a] = [$aP]%`]

    [` [$b] = [$bP]%`]

END_PGML_SOLUTION

ENDDOCUMENT();


